[
    {
        "content": "<p>I made a <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/basic-cli/pull/397\">proposed overhaul</a> of the basic-cli Cmd API.</p>\n<p>The old <code>output!</code> function required people to write <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/www.roc-lang.org/blob/22443df850f2187d1f2ddf9c2b87ac6621aff4f5/website/build_website.roc#L150\">substantial scaffolding code</a> just to see human readable stderr of a command in case it failed. With the new <code>exec_output!</code>, all the info you typically want is included in the error. This works well with just <code>?</code>, for convenient scripting.<br>\n<code>output!</code> used to return:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">status</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">I32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">InternalIOErr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">IOErr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">stdout</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">U8</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">stderr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">U8</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>exec_output!</code> now returns <code>Ok({stdout_utf8 : Str, stderr_utf8_lossy : Str})</code> if the exit code (=status) is 0, if not, the exit code is included in the error.</p>\n<p><code>exec_output_bytes!</code> was added to get stdout and stderr in bytes, similar to the old <code>output!</code>, for fine grained control or max perf.</p>\n<p><code>exec!</code> got nicer errors.</p>\n<p><code>exec_cmd!</code> for when you want to execute your command with specific env vars and forward stdout, stderr, and stdin directly to your terminal.</p>\n<p><code>status!</code> was renamed to <code>exec_exit_code!</code> and given nicer errors as well.</p>\n<p>What do you think?</p>",
        "id": 535358796,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1755709963
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Comparing to the old way it looks better! I had not used the <code>exec</code> yet, so it's hard for me to evaluate this change pragmatically.</p>",
        "id": 535561975,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruby",
        "timestamp": 1755802846
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll make a before and after example to make it easier to evaluate</p>",
        "id": 535642096,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1755852974
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">exec</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"date\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s\">\"-X\"</span><span class=\"p\">])</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>before:</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>date: invalid option -- &#39;X&#39;\nTry &#39;date --help&#39; for more information.\n\nProgram exited with error:\n\n    ❌ CmdStatusErr (Other &quot;Non-zero exit code: 1&quot;)\n</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>after:</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>date: invalid option -- &#39;X&#39;\nTry &#39;date --help&#39; for more information.\n\nProgram exited with error:\n\n    ❌ ExecFailed {command: &quot;date -X&quot;, exit_code: 1}\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 535816230,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1755966771
    },
    {
        "content": "<ul>\n<li>before:</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">run_cmd_w_output</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"date\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s\">\"-X\"</span><span class=\"p\">])</span><span class=\"o\">?</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># You need this whole function to get usable output on error</span>\n<span class=\"nx\">run_cmd_w_output</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Str</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Str</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nx\">BadCmdOutput</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">)]</span><span class=\"nx\">_</span>\n<span class=\"nx\">run_cmd_w_output</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"nx\">cmd_str</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">args</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">cmd_out</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">cmd_str</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">args</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">args</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">output</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">stdout_utf8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">from_utf8_lossy</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">cmd_out</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">stdout</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">when</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">cmd_out</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">status</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">is</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nx\">Ok</span><span class=\"nf\">(0) -&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nx\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">stdout_utf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nx\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nv\">stderr_utf8</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Str</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">from_utf8_lossy</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">cmd_out</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">stderr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nv\">err_data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"s\">\"\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"s\">                Cmd `${cmd_str} ${Str.join_with(args, \" \")}` failed:</span>\n<span class=\"s\">                - status: ${Inspect.to_str(cmd_out.status)}</span>\n<span class=\"s\">                - stdout: ${stdout_utf8}</span>\n<span class=\"s\">                - stderr: ${stderr_utf8}</span>\n<span class=\"s\">                \"\"\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nx\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">BadCmdOutput</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">err_data</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Program exited with error:\n\n    ❌ BadCmdOutput &quot;Cmd `date -X` failed:\n- status: (Err (Other &quot;Non-zero exit code: 1&quot;))\n- stdout:\n- stderr: date: invalid option -- &#39;X&#39;\nTry &#39;date --help&#39; for more information.\n&quot;\n</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>after:</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"date\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">arg</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"-X\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">exec_output</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">?</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Program exited with error:\n\n    ❌ NonZeroExitCode {command: &quot;{ cmd: date, args: -X }&quot;, exit_code: 1, stderr_utf8_lossy: &quot;date: invalid option -- &#39;X&#39;\nTry &#39;date --help&#39; for more information.\n&quot;, stdout_utf8_lossy: &quot;&quot;}\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 535816266,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1755966811
    },
    {
        "content": "<ul>\n<li>before:</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">exit_code</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"dat\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">arg</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"-X\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">status</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">?</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Program exited with error:\n\n    ❌ CmdStatusErr NotFound\n</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>after:</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"CoffeeScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">exit_code</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"dat\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">arg</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"-X\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">Cmd</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nx\">exec_exit_code</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">?</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Program exited with error:\n\n    ❌ FailedToGetExitCode {command: &quot;{ cmd: dat, args: -X }&quot;, err: NotFound}\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 535817247,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1755968080
    },
    {
